 <br>
<br>
<br>
This is a version that fixes issues introduced in yesterday's patch.<br>
<br>
<br>
NEW THINGS AND BUG FIXES<br>
<br>
- Please note that all characters have had their Realm Abilities and points reset. You will now have no Realm Abilities, but will have the proper amount of points to train in them once again. Pendragon only.<br>
<br>
- There was a systemic problem with handing items to NPCs (used in repairs, enchantments, quests - basically anything that involved a player handing an item to an NPC). This has been fixed. Pendragon only.<br>
<br>
- There were some problems with Realm Ability points clearing out when you zoned. This has been fixed. Pendragon only.<br>
<br>
- Please note that there is a known bug that when you create a new character on Pendragon, you see its model in the character description screen. This is not fixed yet, but we will address it soon.<br>
<br>
- There were some problems with the accept/decline dialog box that caused it to look doubled, and act inconsistently. This has been fixed. Pendragon only.<br>
<br>
- Mana level in the small group window now displays correctly once again. Pendragon only.<br>
<br>
- Level 50 armors are now in for all classes except Champion and Ranger, which will be in shortly.<br>
<br>
- The performance meter now works properly once again. Pendragon bug only.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
SPELL/ABILITY SYSTEM NOTES<br>
<br>
- Resistances now affect the duration of debuffs, which include mez/root/snare/stun. Positive amounts in your bonus page will reduce the duration of debuffs *of that damage type* by the listed percent. Negative amounts will increase the duration of debuffs except for mesmerize, stun and root/snare. This means that mez/root/snare/stun duration will never be longer than they were previous to this update - but if you are resistant to a particular one, its duration will be shorter. These bonuses are cumulative with realm ability magical resistance.<br>
<br>
- Dualist's Reflexes (realm ability) should no longer cause left-axe users to hit for max damage every hit.<br>
<br>
- Realm ability lists have been revised again. Hopefully everyone has all their pre-reqs available, and all classes are getting the right abilities listed.<br>
<br>
- Lifetaps should no longer list x10 damage when delved.<br>
<br>
